The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Day IV washed out
Bulawayo: The fourth day of the second Test between Zimbabwe and Bangladesh was abandoned without a ball bowled on Sunday because of rain. Captains Heath Streak and Habibul Bashar were to confer about whether to agree that a result was not possible with only one more days play left. An agreement would lead to the match being abandoned, subject to approval by the Match Referee. The first two days were also abandoned due to weather and only three hours of play were possible on Saturday. Aussie security trip A three-member Aussie delegation will tour Zimbabwe to asseess security arrangements ahead of their tour in May.  (AGENCIES)  Copyright 
